concepts.term: the problem is, you also get cross-product terms when expanding.

evidence: The cross terms are messy, and hence the SPECT data model contains source-position-dependent weighting factors, even if you know the attenuation background.
SLIDE_TEXT: 'The cross terms mean the data model for SPECT includes weighting factors that still depend on the source positions, even when you know the attenuation background.'
